name_PD: Shape Changing: Enhanced Elongation and Shape Recovery
description_PD: The behavior involves the shape-changing properties of SMP composites with nanosilica, where enhanced elongation and high shape recovery allow for flexible and durable designs in products such as wearables or smart devices.

name_PD: Shape Shifting: Tunable 3D Geometries in Intelligent Devices
description_PD: This behavior involves the shape-shifting capabilities of SMPs, where 3D printed objects can smoothly transition between different forms, enabling innovative designs for intelligent photonic and electronic devices.

name_PD: Shape Changing: Elongation and Phase Transformation in NiTi Alloys
description_PD: The behavior of NiTi alloys involves shape changes through elongation and phase transformation, allowing designers to create adaptive smart structures for various applications like robotics and biomedical devices.

name_PD: Shape Changing: Elongation and Hardening in Custom Steel for High-Strength Applications
description_PD: The behavior involves shape-changing through controlled elongation and in situ hardening of maraging steel during 3D printing, offering designers enhanced material strength and flexibility for high-stress applications like aerospace or automotive.

name_PD: Shape Shifting: Self-Forming Curvature in 4D Textiles
description_PD: This behavior enables 4D textiles to self-form into permanent shapes upon thermal stimulation, creating complex designs with dynamic curvatures for wearable products like wrist supports.

name_PD: Shape Shifting: Sequential Elongation and Bending in Auxetic Grids
description_PD: This behavior allows the 4D-printed auxetic structures to autonomously shift between in-plane elongation and out-of-plane bending, enabling dynamic, programmable shape changes for complex applications in various fields.

name_PD: Shape Changing: Large Deformation and Controlled Motion in Soft-Magnetic Composites
description_PD: This behavior involves large-scale shape changes such as deformation and controlled motion in flexible anisotropic soft-magnetic composites, enabling dynamic and adaptable designs for smart sensors and actuators.

name_PD: Shape Changing: Magnetic Shape Recovery in Nanocomposites
description_PD: This behavior involves remotely triggered shape recovery through magnetic stimulation, allowing designers to create responsive 3D and 4D printed objects that can change form for applications such as smart devices and medical tools.

name_PD: Shape Changing: Elongation and Recovery in PETG-PBAT Blends
description_PD: This behavior highlights the material’s ability to undergo elongation and fast shape recovery, enabling designers to create flexible and resilient products, particularly for applications requiring durable yet adaptable components.

name_PD: Shape Changing: Elongation and Recovery in Dual-Polymer Composites
description_PD: This behavior highlights the ability of PVC-PP composites to change their shape through elongation and then recover, which enhances the flexibility and durability of products designed for industries like automotive and aerospace.

name_PE: Shape Changing: Rapid Curing and Shape Memory Retention
description_PE: This behavior focuses on the rapid curing and shape memory retention in nanosilica-enhanced SMPs, allowing faster and more efficient production of 4D printed parts without compromising on elongation or mechanical properties.

name_PE: Shape Changing: Elongation and Shape Memory Control in SMP Fabrication
description_PE: This behavior focuses on precise shape-changing properties, such as elongation and shape recovery, during digital light fabrication of SMPs, optimizing the material’s mechanical performance in a rapid production process.

name_PE: Shape Changing: Grain Refinement and Phase Control in 4D Printing
description_PE: This behavior focuses on the shape-changing properties achieved through laser powder bed fusion, where grain refinement and phase transformation are controlled to optimize mechanical properties like tensile strength and elongation.

name_PE: Shape Changing: In Situ Precipitation and Elongation in Laser Additive Manufacturing
description_PE: This behavior focuses on in situ precipitation and elongation during the laser additive manufacturing process, where controlled deposition and heat treatment enable precise material strengthening without post-processing.

name_PE: Shape Changing: Elongation-Controlled Forming in 4D Printed Textiles
description_PE: The behavior involves shape changes where the relative elongation of Lycra fabric and the thickness of PLA layers control the final form of the composite, enhancing precision and efficiency in 4D printing processes.

name_PE: Shape Changing: Temperature-Responsive Shape Recovery in Photopolymer Structures
description_PE: The behavior leverages the temperature memory effect (TME) to precisely control the recovery of 4D-printed structures, enabling efficient and programmable deformation and recovery based on temperature stimuli.

name_PE: Shape Changing: Elongation and Variable Stiffness in Magnetic-Enhanced Printing
description_PE: The behavior focuses on achieving high elongation and variable stiffness during the fabrication process of soft-magnetic composites, optimizing printability while maintaining strong magnetic properties.

name_PE: Shape Changing: Controlled Elongation and Tensile Strength in Granule-Based FDM Printing
description_PE: The behavior emphasizes the precise control of elongation and tensile strength in nanocomposite filaments during the FDM printing process, ensuring structural integrity while incorporating nanoparticles.

name_PE: Shape Changing: Controlled Melt Flow and Printability in Granule-Based 3D Printing
description_PE: The behavior focuses on the shape-changing dynamics during the 3D printing process, where controlling the melt flow and optimizing printability parameters enable precise and uniform output with enhanced tensile strength and elongation.

name_PE: Shape Changing: Tensile Strength and Elongation in Composite Filaments
description_PE: The behavior focuses on the shape-changing properties during the printing process, where tensile strength and elongation play a crucial role in ensuring the durability and effectiveness of the produced parts in fused filament fabrication.

name_MS: Shape Changing: Nanosilica-Induced Elongation and Plasticity Control
description_MS: The behavior involves enhanced elongation and controlled plasticizing effects due to the interaction between nanosilica and polymer chains, leading to improved mechanical performance and shape memory in reinforced SMP composites.

name_MS: Shape Changing: Spatio-Temporal Tuning of SMP Properties
description_MS: The behavior centers on spatio-temporally tuned shape-changing capabilities, like elongation and shape memory response, allowing fine control of material properties such as transition temperature and modulus in a single construct.

name_MS: Shape Changing: Phase Transition and Mechanical Property Enhancement in NiTi SMAs
description_MS: The behavior involves phase transformation from B2 to B19', resulting in improved mechanical properties like tensile strength and elongation, making NiTi SMAs highly suitable for 4D printing applications requiring graded transformations.

name_MS: Shape Changing: In Situ Precipitation Hardening and Uniform Elongation in Fe-Ni-Ti-Al Alloys
description_MS: The behavior involves in situ precipitation hardening and uniform elongation within the maraging steel matrix, where tailored deposition and thermal cycles lead to the formation of precipitates, enhancing the steel's mechanical properties during printing.

name_MS: Shape Changing: Thermal Responsiveness and Reversible Transformation
description_MS: The behavior observed in the PLA-Lycra composite involves reversible shape-changing under thermal stimuli, where the material transitions between multiple temporary shapes and a permanent shape, driven by thermal responsiveness.

name_MS: Shape Changing: Thermoviscoelastic Deformation and Recovery in Auxetic Polymers
description_MS: This behavior describes the complex thermoviscoelastic deformation and recovery process in auxetic polymers, where the material undergoes controlled shape changes and recovers autonomously over a wide range of temperatures, aided by the temperature memory effect (TME).

name_MS: Shape Shifting: Anisotropic Magnetic Response in FASMC
description_MS: This behavior describes the shape shifting and anisotropic magnetic response of flexible anisotropic soft-magnetic composites, where external magnetic fields induce controlled deformation and stiffness changes, critical for advanced materials in actuators and sensors.

name_MS: Shape Changing: Enhanced Shape-Memory with Magnetic and Heat Stimulation
description_MS: This behavior involves shape recovery in PETG-ABS-Fe3O4 nanocomposites when exposed to magnetic and heat stimulation, improving the shape-memory effect and heat transfer for advanced material applications.

name_MS: Shape Changing: Enhanced Elasticity and Shape Recovery in PETG-PBAT Composites
description_MS: This behavior involves the improved elasticity and faster shape recovery of PETG-PBAT composites, driven by the material’s ability to blend immiscibly yet compatibly, enhancing mechanical properties and thermomechanical performance.

name_MS: Shape Changing: Elastic Deformation and Shape Memory Recovery in Polymers
description_MS: The behavior involves elastic deformation and one-way shape memory, where the PVC-PP composites exhibit significant elongation and recover their shape under controlled conditions, critical for mechanical and thermal performance.
